# pnpm uses a symlinked, isolated node_modules by default. Vitest/Vite resolve
# symlinks to their real path, and under that layout the prosemirror-* packages
# (pulled in transitively via @tiptap/pm) end up loaded as TWO module instances,
# which trips ProseMirror's keyed-plugin identity check at runtime:
#   RangeError: Adding different instances of a keyed plugin (plugin$)
#
# `node-linker=hoisted` makes pnpm lay out a FLAT node_modules with real
# directories, exactly like npm — so the resolver dedupes to a single instance.
# We keep pnpm's real wins (global content-addressable store + hardlinks for
# disk savings, fast installs, single lockfile, strict CLI). The only thing we
# trade away vs. the default isolated linker is phantom-dependency detection,
# which this project (previously on npm) never relied on.
node-linker=hoisted
